Paraben Tolerance - Figure

CorrectedResults %>%
  filter(Isolate=="P. gelicola" & !(Well %in% c("H02", "B02", "D03", "D06"))) %>% # Remove specific wells if they're funky
  mutate(Carbon = case_when(Carbon=="B" ~ "Butylparaben",
                            Carbon=="D" ~ "Diazolidinyl Urea",
                            Carbon=="E" ~ "Ethylparaben",
                            Carbon=="GL" ~ "Glucose",
                            Carbon=="M" ~ "Methylparaben",
                            Carbon=="N" ~ "No Additional Carbon Control",
                            Carbon=="P" ~ "Propylparaben"),
         Carbon = factor(Carbon, levels=c("No Additional Carbon Control",
                                             "Glucose", "Methylparaben",
                                             "Ethylparaben", "Propylparaben",
                                             "Butylparaben", "Diazolidinyl Urea"))) %>%
  ggplot() +
  aes(x=ElapsedTime, y=CorrectedAbsorbance, color=Concentration) +
  geom_point(alpha=0.5, size=0.8) +
  geom_smooth(se=FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(facets=vars(Carbon)) +
  labs(x="Hours", y="OD", color="Concentration") +
  theme_classic() + scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired")

Save OD Results in one file

CorrectedResults %>%
  select(Well, Isolate, Concentration, Carbon, Rep, Media, Note, ElapsedTime, CorrectedAbsorbance) %>%
  arrange(ElapsedTime) %>%
  mutate(ElapsedTime=paste(round(ElapsedTime, 0), "hours", sep=""),
          CorrectedAbsorbance=round(CorrectedAbsorbance, 2)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from=ElapsedTime,values_from=CorrectedAbsorbance) %>%
  write_delim("AgglomeratedResults.csv", delim=",")

Use GrowthCurver to Model Different Treatments

Treatments <- CorrectedResults %>%
  filter(Isolate != "None") %>%  #Remove blanks
  pull(Media) %>% unique()
PredictedValues <- data.frame(t = 0:max(CorrectedResults$ElapsedTime)) # What timepoints to predict values from fitted model for?
Models <- NULL
for (i in Treatments){
  ResultsForModel <- CorrectedResults %>%
    filter(Isolate=="P. gelicola" & !(Well %in% c("H02", "B02", "D03", "D06"))) %>%
    filter(Media==i) %>%
    filter(ElapsedTime<=max(CorrectedResults$ElapsedTime)) %>%
    ungroup() %>% select(t=ElapsedTime, CorrectedAbsorbance)
  if (range(ResultsForModel$CorrectedAbsorbance)[2] - range(ResultsForModel$CorrectedAbsorbance)[1] > 0.05){ # Only determine model if treatment has grown at least 0.05 OD
    Model <- growthcurver::SummarizeGrowth(data_t=ResultsForModel$t, 
                                         data_n=ResultsForModel$CorrectedAbsorbance)
    Models[[i]] <- Model$vals
    PredictedValues[[i]] <- predict(Model$model, newdata = list(t=PredictedValues$t))
  } else {
    PredictedValues[[i]] <- mean(ResultsForModel$CorrectedAbsorbance)
  }
}

PredictedValues %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=2:ncol(.), names_to="Media", values_to="OD") %>%
  rename(ElapsedTime=t) %>%
  mutate(Carbon=case_when(Media=="0.1 x TSB" ~ "N",
                          TRUE ~ str_split_i(Media, " ", 3)),
         Concentration=case_when(Media=="0.1 x TSB" ~ "N",
                          TRUE ~ paste(str_split_i(Media, " ", 1), "mM"))) %>%
  full_join(., filter(CorrectedResults, Isolate != "None")) %>%
  filter(!(Well %in% c("H02", "B02", "D03", "D06"))) %>%
  mutate(Carbon = case_when(Carbon=="B" ~ "Butylparaben",
                            Carbon=="D" ~ "Diazolidinyl Urea",

         Carbon = factor(Carbon, levels=c("No Additional Carbon Control",
